          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2024-01-11 23:48:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFailed enforced test custom-1002 on RHEL 8.8/x86_64, RHEL 8.9/x86_64 uploaded by Onyx Autotest 2 from onyx-116vm1: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/f595f7e9-0ad8-4712-b16c-6193e665e0e2 ran 3 tests.  1 tests failed: sanity-hsm.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3edf75803fdf0a8c77e52271eb02ef704c769ea7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-01-12 01:12:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt looks like the interop testing with a new client and old server failed a number of tests - 114, 250, 409a, 500:\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/8289d4d2-9b63-457c-9b44-41a7e86e9f31\n\nHowever, the most recent set of interop tests for master with 2.12.9 or 2.14.0 servers also failed the same tests - 114, 250, 409a, 500:\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/40b94bb3-8dc4-4a40-b06a-7f0e8d4c4e7a\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/4c1e82bf-073b-46c6-84fa-bfa9667c4de6\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1f2455e2-2482-44a2-ba60-89aba7ecf45d\nhttps://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/5d65c29a-af51-431e-86a2-d3d56df87fe2\n\nThere is an open ticket LU-15762 for test_500, but not for the other subtests.  It would be good if someone with HSM knowledge would look at them to determine if these are real interop issues/regressions, or just new subtests that depend on functionality that could be skipped based on the server version.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "013604045de7252deb6341ac602ff6899d902115",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
